snippet.title: "TROUBLE" an original song about COVID, MONEY, POWER, and CONROL | freedom rally live performance
snippet.description:
I recently performed live at a local freedom rally in my city of Prince George in British Columbia, Canada where the mandates are out of control. Man did it feel good to be able to sing my heart out for a crowd of people as I am currently banned from performing in indoor businesses because of personal medical decisions. 

We don't need a two-tier society, we need unity.

♪ check out my song about cancer and big pharma https://youtu.be/-EoF4OcmXdY ♪
Instagram📸@herhabitschannel  https://www.instagram.com/herhabitschannel/
TikTok⏰@herhabitschannel https://www.tiktok.com/@herhabitschannel
---------------------------------
lyrics:

Oh I should have known
you were trouble
want nothing more than control
sad the world can't see
the wolf in clothes of sheep
and we're just sheep
I'm not buying in to your schemes
to fulfill all your fantasies
you can't touch me

too censored to be true
too fake to be news
but now I know the truth

and work me like a machine
till I forget my dreams
I blame you
you think I am nothing more
than human capital
cause you just want money

I should have known, oh I should have known 
you were trouble

too censored to be true
too fake to be news
but now I know the truth
